# it-works-regenerator-server

HTTP server version of [it-works-regenerator-html](https://github.com/ontouchstart/it-works-regenerator-html)

# example

`test.js`

``` js
var g = gen(100);

var y = g.next();
while(1) {
  if(y.done) break;
  console.log(y.value);
  y = g.next();
}
```

`index.html`

``` html
<html>
  <head>
    <title>it-works-regenerator</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>
      Please view the result in JavaScript console
    </h1>
    <script src="main.js"></script>
    <script src="test.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
```

`server.js`

``` js
var server = require('it-works-regenerator-server');
var port = process.env.PORT || 8888;
server.listen(port, 'localhost');
console.log('server listen to http://localhost:' + port);
```
